    "As depicted in Fig. 4, a surge in scholarly attention to AI in educational research is evident from 2008 to 2013.",
    "Notably, this trend is particularly pronounced in publications on SpringerLink, setting it apart from other sources.",
    "From 2014 to 2022, there was a greater trend in AI research in education.",
    "According to Springer Link, WoS, IEEE, and Nigerian publications released between 2014 and 2022 had the most papers on AI in education.",
    "This observation underscores a discernible surge in Nigeria's appetite for integrating AI technology into the education sector, signaling an increasing demand for innovative educational solutions.Preceding studies in AI methodology have employed various algorithms, including Artificial Neural Networks (ANN), decision trees, logistic regression, Support Vector Machines (SVM), ensembles/bagging (random forest), fuzzy logic, and other data mining and machine learning techniques."
